<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 832.85/37</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-03T12:00:00-03:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1917, noon</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 4, 1 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>President of Brazil yesterday issued a decree placing all German
                                merchant vessels anchored in Brazilian ports under the Brazilian
                                flag and directing that they be prepared for sea as soon as
                                possible. The vessels in Rio de Janeiro harbor have already been
                                appropriated, and others under control of Lloyd Brasileiro Company
                                which is under the direction of Ministry of Finance. Appropriation
                                and transfer of flag effected without opposition. Appropriation of
                                vessels in other ports under way.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MEV1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>